    "**Reading the scale table.**\n",
    "\n",
    "* **GT** is the truth from manual landmark Procrustes (`fit_anisotropic_similarity` on `landmarks_qced.csv`).\n",
    "* **LP + sz pin** is what Stage A + v2-S02 iter-7 gives us — the warmstart that all four methods consume.  Both axes are within ±1 % of GT (sz pin's mean |err| was 0.040 µm = 1.4 % across the 6 subjects).\n",
    "* **M3-ICP-locked** = LP + sz pin by construction (only SE(3) is fit on top, no scale residual).\n",
    "* **C5** typically lands within a few % of GT — its members re-fit affine but density-priority dispatch picks the closer one.\n",
    "* **P3** drifts substantially in z.  RANSAC's 4-point aniso-affine fit is *underdetermined* in sz when the 4 correspondences span only ~150 µm of depth (typical) and have ~5 µm noise per point: the fit absorbs the noise into a scale stretch.  Refitting on inliers locks in the wrong sz across the entire pair list.  Final sz can be 10–30 % off, which propagates to ≥ 30 µm z-error per pair → r@20 collapses.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the structural reason **M3-ICP wins by locking what was already correct**.  The locked prior + sz pin is right (within 1 %); P3 throws that away and rederives sxy/sz from noisy NN matches; M3-ICP keeps it."
