    "* **782149 (fail)** — `d_med` *increases* from ~89 µm to ~91 µm; `|Δt|` *grows* from ~33 µm to ~98 µm; rotation `Δθ` reaches 3.17°.  ICP **diverges**.  The warmstart's NN graph at iter 0 already has wrong matches everywhere (median 89 µm is more than typical cell-cell spacing of ~30 µm), and each Procrustes step on a wrong-correspondence set drives the cloud further from truth.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Both failure modes share one root cause: warmstart-to-truth distance > convergence radius.**  The convergence radius for rigid ICP on 3D point clouds is roughly the median nearest-neighbour distance in HCR (typically 15-25 µm here).  When the LP+sz-pin warmstart starts above that band, NN matches are statistically wrong from iter 0 and Procrustes will lock in or amplify the error."
